23"""Aiobungie Interfaces provides abstracted objects for implementations."""

25from __future__ import annotations
26
27__all__: tuple[str, ...] = ("RESTInterface", "FactoryInterface")

29from .factory import FactoryInterface
30from .rest import RESTInterface
class RESTInterface(aiobungie.traits.RESTful, abc.ABC): 
  49class RESTInterface(traits.RESTful, abc.ABC):
  50    """An API interface for the rest only client implementation."""
  51
  52    __slots__ = ()
  53
  54    if typing.TYPE_CHECKING:
  55
  56        async def __aenter__(self) -> RESTInterface:
  57            ...
  58
  59        async def __aexit__(
  60            self,
  61            exception_type: typing.Optional[type[BaseException]],
  62            exception: typing.Optional[BaseException],
  63            exception_traceback: typing.Optional[types.TracebackType],
  64        ) -> None:
  65            ...
  66
  67    @abc.abstractmethod
  68    async def read_manifest_bytes(self, language: str = "en", /) -> bytes:
  69        """Read raw manifest SQLite database bytes response.
  70
  71        This method can be used to write the bytes to zipped file
  72        and then extract it to get the manifest content.
  73
  74        Parameters
  75        ----------
  76        language : `str`
  77            The manifest database language bytes to get.
  78
  79        Returns
  80        -------
  81        `bytes`
  82            The bytes to read and write the manifest database.
  83        """
  84
  85    @abc.abstractmethod
  86    async def fetch_manifest_path(self) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
  87        """Fetch the manifest JSON paths.
  88
  89        Returns
  90        -------
  91        `typedefs.JSONObject`
  92            The manifest JSON paths.
  93        """
  94
  95    @abc.abstractmethod
  96    async def download_json_manifest(
  97        self,
  98        file_name: str = "manifest",
  99        path: typing.Union[str, pathlib.Path] = ".",
 100        language: str = "en",
 101    ) -> None:
 102        """Download the Bungie manifest json file.
 103
 104        Parameters
 105        ----------
 106        file_name: `str`
 107            The file name to save the manifest json file. Default is `manifest`.
 108        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
 109            The path to save the manifest json file. Default is the current directory. Example `"D:/"`
 110        language: `str`
 111            The manifest database language bytes to get. Default is English.
 112        """
 113
 114    @abc.abstractmethod
 115    async def download_manifest(
 116        self,
 117        language: str = "en",
 118        name: str = "manifest",
 119        path: typing.Union[str, pathlib.Path] = ".",
 120        *,
 121        force: bool = False,
 122    ) -> None:
 123        """A helper method to download the manifest.
 124
 125        Note
 126        ----
 127        This method downloads the sqlite database and not JSON.
 128        Use `RESTInterface.download_json_manifest` for the JSON version.
 129
 130        Parameters
 131        ----------
 132        language : `str`
 133            The manifest language to download, Default is english.
 134        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
 135            The path to save the manifest sqlite database. Example `"D:/"`, Default is the current directory.
 136        name : `str`
 137            The manifest database file name. Default is `manifest`
 138        force : `bool`
 139            Whether to force the download. Default is `False`. However if set to true the old
 140            file will get removed and a new one will being to download.
 141
 142        Returns
 143        --------
 144        `None`
 145
 146        Raises
 147        ------
 148        `FileNotFoundError`
 149            If the manifest file exists and `force` is `False`.
 150        `ValueError`
 151            If the provided language was not recognized.
 152        """
 153
 154    @abc.abstractmethod
 155    async def fetch_manifest_version(self) -> str:
 156        """Fetch the manifest version.
 157
 158        Returns
 159        -------
 160        `str`
 161            The manifest version.
 162        """

 164    @abc.abstractmethod
 165    async def fetch_bungie_user(self, id: int) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 166        """Fetch a Bungie user by their id.
 167
 168        Parameters
 169        ----------
 170        id: `int`
 171            The user id.
 172
 173        Returns
 174        -------
 175        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 176            A JSON object of users objects.
 177
 178        Raises
 179        ------
 180        `aiobungie.error.NotFound`
 181            The user was not found.
 182        """

 185    async def search_users(self, name: str, /) -> typedefs.JSONObject:

 192
 193        Returns
 194        -------
 195        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`

 203        """

 215    @abc.abstractmethod
 216    async def fetch_hardlinked_credentials(
 217        self,
 218        credential: int,
 219        type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.CredentialType] = enums.CredentialType.STEAMID,
 220        /,
 221    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 222        """Gets any hard linked membership given a credential.
 223
 224        Only works for credentials that are public just `aiobungie.CredentialType.STEAMID` right now.
 225        Cross Save aware.
 226
 227        Parameters
 228        ----------
 229        credential: `int`
 230            A valid SteamID64
 231        type: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.CredentialType]`
 232            The crededntial type. This must not be changed
 233            Since its only credential that works "currently"
 234
 235        Returns
 236        -------
 237        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 238            A JSON object of the found user hard linked types.
 239        """

 243        self,

 246        /,
 247    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 248        """Fetch Bungie user's memberships from their id.
 249
 250        Parameters

 268    @abc.abstractmethod
 269    async def fetch_profile(
 270        self,
 271        membership_id: int,
 272        type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType],
 273        components: list[enums.ComponentType],
 274        auth: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 275    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 276        """
 277        Fetch a bungie profile.
 278
 279        Parameters
 280        ----------
 281        membership_id: `int`
 282            The member's id.
 283        type: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
 284            A valid membership type.
 285        components : `list[aiobungie.ComponentType]`
 286            A list of profile components to collect and return.
 287
 288        Other Parameters
 289        ----------------
 290        auth : `typing.Optional[str]`
 291            A bearer access_token to make the request with.
 292            This is optional and limited to components that only requires an Authorization token.
 293
 294        Returns
 295        --------
 296        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 297            A JSON object of the found profile.
 298
 299        Raises
 300        ------
 301        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 302            The provided membership type was invalid.
 303        """
 304
 305    @abc.abstractmethod
 306    async def fetch_player(
 307        self,
 308        name: str,
 309        code: int,
 310        type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType] = enums.MembershipType.ALL,
 311        /,
 312    ) -> typedefs.JSONArray:
 313        """Fetch a Destiny 2 Player.
 314
 315        Parameters
 316        -----------
 317        name: `str`
 318            The unique Bungie player name.
 319        code : `int`
 320            The unique Bungie display name code.
 321        type: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
 322            The player's membership type, e,g. XBOX, STEAM, PSN
 323
 324        Returns
 325        --------
 326        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONArray`
 327            A JSON array of the found player's memberships.
 328
 329        Raises
 330        ------
 331        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 332            The player was not found.
 333        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 334            The provided membership type was invalid.
 335        """

 337    @abc.abstractmethod
 338    async def fetch_character(
 339        self,
 340        member_id: int,
 341        membership_type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType],
 342        character_id: int,
 343        components: list[enums.ComponentType],
 344        auth: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 345    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 346        """Fetch a Destiny 2 player's characters.
 347
 348        Parameters
 349        ----------
 350        member_id: `int`
 351            A valid bungie member id.
 352        membership_type: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.internal.enums.MembershipType]`
 353            The member's membership type.
 354        character_id : `int`
 355            The character id to return.
 356        components: `list[aiobungie.ComponentType]`
 357            A list of character components to collect and return.
 358
 359        Other Parameters
 360        ----------------
 361        auth : `typing.Optional[str]`
 362            A bearer access_token to make the request with.
 363            This is optional and limited to components that only requires an Authorization token.
 364
 365        Returns
 366        -------
 367        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 368            A JSON object of the requested character.
 369
 370        Raises
 371        ------
 372        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 373            The provided membership type was invalid.
 374        """

 376    @abc.abstractmethod
 377    async def fetch_activities(
 378        self,
 379        member_id: int,
 380        character_id: int,
 381        mode: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.GameMode],
 382        membership_type: typedefs.IntAnd[
 383            enums.MembershipType
 384        ] = enums.MembershipType.ALL,
 385        *,
 386        page: int = 1,
 387        limit: int = 1,
 388    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 389        """Fetch a Destiny 2 activity for the specified user id and character.
 390
 391        Parameters
 392        ----------
 393        member_id: `int`
 394            The user id that starts with `4611`.
 395        character_id: `int`
 396            The id of the character to retrieve.
 397        mode: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.GameMode]`
 398            This parameter filters the game mode, Nightfall, Strike, Iron Banner, etc.
 399
 400        Other Parameters
 401        ----------------
 402        membership_type: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.internal.enums.MembershipType]`
 403            The Member ship type, if nothing was passed than it will return all.
 404        page: `int`
 405            The page number. Default to `1`
 406        limit: `int`
 407            Limit the returned result. Default to `1`
 408
 409        Returns
 410        -------
 411        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 412            A JSON object of the player's activities.
 413
 414        Raises
 415        ------
 416        `aiobungie.error.NotFound`
 417            The activity was not found.
 418
 419        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 420            The provided membership type was invalid.
 421        """
 422

 438    @abc.abstractmethod
 439    async def fetch_clan_from_id(
 440        self, id: int, /, access_token: typing.Optional[str] = None
 441    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 442        """Fetch a Bungie Clan by its id.
 443
 444        Parameters
 445        -----------
 446        id : `int`
 447            The clan id.
 448
 449        Other Parameters
 450        ----------------
 451        access_token : `typing.Optional[str]`
 452            An optional access token to make the request with.
 453
 454            If the token was bound to a member of the clan,
 455            This field `aiobungie.crates.Clan.current_user_membership` will be available
 456            and will return the membership of the user who made this request.
 457
 458        Returns
 459        --------
 460        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 461            A JSON object of the clan.
 462
 463        Raises
 464        ------
 465        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 466            The clan was not found.
 467        """
 468
 469    @abc.abstractmethod
 470    async def fetch_clan(
 471        self,
 472        name: str,
 473        /,
 474        access_token: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 475        *,
 476        type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.GroupType] = enums.GroupType.CLAN,
 477    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 478        """Fetch a Clan by its name.
 479        This method will return the first clan found with given name name.
 480
 481        Parameters
 482        ----------
 483        name : `str`
 484            The clan name.
 485
 486        Other Parameters
 487        ----------------
 488        access_token : `typing.Optional[str]`
 489            An optional access token to make the request with.
 490
 491            If the token was bound to a member of the clan,
 492            This field `aiobungie.crates.Clan.current_user_membership` will be available
 493            and will return the membership of the user who made this request.
 494        type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.GroupType]`
 495            The group type, Default is one.
 496
 497        Returns
 498        -------
 499        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 500            A JSON object of the clan.
 501
 502        Raises
 503        ------
 504        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 505            The clan was not found.
 506        """
 507

 543    @abc.abstractmethod
 544    async def fetch_groups_for_member(
 545        self,
 546        member_id: int,
 547        member_type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType],
 548        /,
 549        *,
 550        filter: int = 0,
 551        group_type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.GroupType] = enums.GroupType.CLAN,
 552    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 553        """Fetch the information about the groups for a member.
 554
 555        Parameters
 556        ----------
 557        member_id : `int`
 558            The member's id
 559        member_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
 560            The member's membership type.
 561
 562        Other Parameters
 563        ----------------
 564        filter : `builsins.int`
 565            Filter apply to list of joined groups. This Default to `0`
 566        group_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.GroupType]`
 567            The group's type.
 568            This is always set to `aiobungie.GroupType.CLAN` and should not be changed.
 569
 570        Returns
 571        -------
 572        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 573            A JSON object of an array of the member's membership data and groups data.
 574        """

 601            This is always set to `aiobungie.GroupType.CLAN` and should not be changed.

 603        Returns

 609    @abc.abstractmethod
 610    async def fetch_clan_members(
 611        self,
 612        clan_id: int,
 613        /,
 614        *,
 615        name: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 616        type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType] = enums.MembershipType.NONE,
 617    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 618        """Fetch all Bungie Clan members.
 619
 620        Parameters
 621        ----------
 622        clan_id : `builsins.int`
 623            The clans id
 624
 625        Other Parameters
 626        ----------------
 627        name : `typing.Optional[str]`
 628            If provided, Only players matching this name will be returned.
 629        type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
 630            An optional clan member's membership type.
 631            Default is set to `aiobungie.MembershipType.NONE`
 632            Which returns the first matched clan member by their name.
 633
 634        Returns
 635        -------
 636        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 637            A JSON object of an array of clan members.
 638
 639        Raises
 640        ------
 641        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 642            The clan was not found.
 643        """
 644

 713        *,
 714        all: bool = False,
 715    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 716        """Returns a summary information about all profiles linked to the requested member.
 717
 718        The passed membership id/type maybe a Bungie.Net membership or a Destiny memberships.

 727        member_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`

 739        Returns

 952    @abc.abstractmethod
 953    async def edit_clan_options(
 954        self,
 955        access_token: str,
 956        /,
 957        group_id: int,
 958        *,
 959        invite_permissions_override: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
 960        update_culture_permissionOverride: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
 961        host_guided_game_permission_override: typedefs.NoneOr[
 962            typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]
 963        ] = None,
 964        update_banner_permission_override: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
 965        join_level: typedefs.NoneOr[typedefs.IntAnd[enums.ClanMemberType]] = None,
 966    ) -> None:
 967        """Edit the clan options.
 968
 969        Notes
 970        -----
 971        * This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: `AdminGroups` scope.
 972        * All arguments will default to `None` if not provided. This does not include `access_token` and `group_id`
 973
 974        Parameters
 975        ----------
 976        access_token : `str`
 977            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
 978        group_id: `int`
 979            The group id.
 980
 981        Other Parameters
 982        ----------------
 983        invite_permissions_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
 984            Minimum Member Level allowed to invite new members to group
 985            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
 986            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
 987            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
 988        update_culture_permissionOverride : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
 989            Minimum Member Level allowed to update group culture
 990            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
 991            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
 992            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
 993        host_guided_game_permission_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
 994            Minimum Member Level allowed to host guided games
 995            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder, Admin
 996            Allowed Overrides: `0` -> None, `1` -> Beginner `2` -> Member.
 997            Default is Member for clans, None for groups, although this means nothing for groups.
 998        update_banner_permission_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
 999            Minimum Member Level allowed to update banner
1000            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
1001            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
1002            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
1003        join_level : `aiobungie.ClanMemberType`
1004            Level to join a member at when accepting an invite, application, or joining an open clan.
1005            Default is `aiobungie.ClanMemberType.BEGINNER`
1006        """

1008    @abc.abstractmethod
1009    async def edit_clan(
1010        self,
1011        access_token: str,
1012        /,
1013        group_id: int,
1014        *,
1015        name: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
1016        about: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
1017        motto: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
1018        theme: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
1019        tags: typedefs.NoneOr[collections.Sequence[str]] = None,
1020        is_public: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
1021        locale: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
1022        avatar_image_index: typedefs.NoneOr[int] = None,
1023        membership_option: typedefs.NoneOr[
1024            typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipOption]
1025        ] = None,
1026        allow_chat: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
1027        chat_security: typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1]] = None,
1028        call_sign: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
1029        homepage: typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]] = None,
1030        enable_invite_messaging_for_admins: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
1031        default_publicity: typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]] = None,
1032        is_public_topic_admin: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
1033    ) -> None:
1034        """Edit a clan.
1035
1036        Notes
1037        -----
1038        * This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: `AdminGroups` scope.
1039        * All arguments will default to `None` if not provided. This does not include `access_token` and `group_id`
1040
1041        Parameters
1042        ----------
1043        access_token : `str`
1044            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1045        group_id: `int`
1046            The group id to edit.
1047
1048        Other Parameters
1049        ----------------
1050        name : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
1051            The name to edit the clan with.
1052        about : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
1053            The about section to edit the clan with.
1054        motto : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
1055            The motto section to edit the clan with.
1056        theme : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
1057            The theme name to edit the clan with.
1058        tags : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[collections.Sequence[str]]`
1059            A sequence of strings to replace the clan tags with.
1060        is_public : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
1061            If provided and set to `True`, The clan will set to private.
1062            If provided and set to `False`, The clan will set to public whether it was or not.
1063        locale : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
1064            The locale section to edit the clan with.
1065        avatar_image_index : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[int]`
1066            The clan avatar image index to edit the clan with.
1067        membership_option : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipOption]]` # noqa: E501 # Line too long
1068            The clan membership option to edit it with.
1069        allow_chat : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
1070            If provided and set to `True`, The clan members will be allowed to chat.
1071            If provided and set to `False`, The clan members will not be allowed to chat.
1072        chat_security : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1]]`
1073            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat security will be edited to `Group` only.
1074            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat security will be edited to `Admin` only.
1075        call_sign : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
1076            The clan call sign to edit it with.
1077        homepage : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
1078            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `Wall`.
1079            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `Forum`.
1080            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `AllianceForum`.
1081        enable_invite_messaging_for_admins : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
1082            ???
1083        default_publicity : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
1084            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Public`.
1085            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Alliance`.
1086            If provided and set to `2`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Private`.
1087        is_public_topic_admin : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
1088            ???
1089        """

1300        security: typing.Literal[0, 1] = 0,
1301        enable_chat: bool = False,
1302    ) -> None:
1303        """Edit the settings of this chat channel.
1304
1305        .. note::
1306            This request requires OAuth2: AdminGroups scope.
1307
1308        Parameters
1309        ----------
1310        access_token : `str`
1311            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1312        group_id : `int`
1313            The given group id.
1314        conversation_id : `int`
1315            The conversation/chat id.
1316
1317        Other parameters
1318        ----------------
1319        name: `aiobungie.UndefinedOr[str]`
1320            The new chat name. Default to `UNDEFINED`
1321        security: `typing.Literal[0, 1]`
1322            The new security level of the chat.
1323
1324            If provided and set to 0, It will be to `Group` only.
1325            If provided and set to 1, It will be `Admins` only.
1326            Default is `0`
1327        enable_chat : `bool`
1328            Whether to enable chatting or not.
1329            If set to `True` then chatting will be enabled. Otherwise it will be disabled.
1330        """
1331

1661    @abc.abstractmethod
1662    async def insert_socket_plug(
1663        self,
1664        action_token: str,
1665        /,
1666        instance_id: int,
1667        plug: typing.Union[builders.PlugSocketBuilder, dict[str, int]],
1668        character_id: int,
1669        membership_type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType],
1670    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
1671        """Insert a plug into a socketed item.
1672
1673        .. note::
1674            OAuth2: AdvancedWriteActions scope is required
1675
1676        Parameters
1677        ----------
1678        action_token : `str`
1679            Action token provided by the AwaGetActionToken API call.
1680        instance_id : `int`
1681            The item instance id that's plug inserted.
1682        plug : `typing.Union[aiobungie.builders.PlugSocketBuilder, dict[str, int]]`
1683            Either a PlugSocketBuilder object or a raw dict contains key, value for the plug entries.
1684
1685        Example
1686        -------
1687        ```py
1688        plug = (
1689            aiobungie.PlugSocketBuilder()
1690            .set_socket_array(0)
1691            .set_socket_index(0)
1692            .set_plug_item(3023847)
1693            .collect()
1694        )
1695        await insert_socket_plug_free(..., plug=plug)
1696        ```
1697        character_id : `int`
1698            The character's id.
1699        membership_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
1700            The membership type.
1701
1702        Returns
1703        -------
1704        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
1705            A JSON object contains the changed item details.
1706
1707        Raises
1708        ------
1709        `aiobungie.Unauthorized`
1710            The access token was wrong or no access token passed.
1711        """
1712

1982    @abc.abstractmethod

2000        access_token : `str`
2001            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
2002        type : `typing.Literal[0, 1]`
2003            Type of the advanced write action. Its either 0 or 1.
2004            If set to 0 that means it `None`. Otherwise if 1 that means its insert plugs.
2005        membership_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
2006            The Destiny membership type of the account to modify.
2007
2008        Other Parameters
2009        ----------------
2010        affected_item_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
2011            Item instance ID the action shall be applied to.
2012            This is optional for all but a new AwaType values.
2013        character_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
2014            The Destiny character ID to perform this action on.
2015
2016        Returns
2017        -------
2018        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
2019            A JSON object response.
2020        """
2021

2155    @abc.abstractmethod
2156    async def fetch_application_api_usage(
2157        self,
2158        access_token: str,
2159        application_id: int,
2160        /,
2161        *,
2162        start: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None,
2163        end: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None,
2164    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
2165        """Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.
2166
2167        Parameters
2168        ----------
2169        access_token : `str`
2170            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
2171        application_id : `int`
2172            The application id to get.
2173
2174        Other Parameters
2175        ----------------
2176        start : `typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]`
2177            A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage.
2178            This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.
2179
2180            If this is left to `None`. It will return the last 24 hours.
2181        end : `typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]`
2182            A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.
2183
2184            If this is left to `None`. It will return `now`.
2185
2186        Example
2187        -------
2188        ```py
2189        import datetime
2190
2191        # Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
2192        await fetch_application_api_usage(
2193            start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10), end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
2194        )
2195        ```
2196
2197        Returns
2198        -------
2199        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
2200            A JSON object of the application usage details.
2201        """

119        path: typing.Union[str, pathlib.Path] = ".",
120        *,
121        force: bool = False,
122    ) -> None:
123        """A helper method to download the manifest.
124
125        Note
126        ----
127        This method downloads the sqlite database and not JSON.
128        Use `RESTInterface.download_json_manifest` for the JSON version.
129
130        Parameters
131        ----------
132        language : `str`
133            The manifest language to download, Default is english.
134        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
135            The path to save the manifest sqlite database. Example `"D:/"`, Default is the current directory.
136        name : `str`
137            The manifest database file name. Default is `manifest`
138        force : `bool`
139            Whether to force the download. Default is `False`. However if set to true the old
140            file will get removed and a new one will being to download.
141
142        Returns
143        --------
144        `None`
145
146        Raises
147        ------
148        `FileNotFoundError`
149            If the manifest file exists and `force` is `False`.
150        `ValueError`
151            If the provided language was not recognized.
152        """

A helper method to download the manifest.

Note

This method downloads the sqlite database and not JSON. Use RESTInterface.download_json_manifest for the JSON version.

Parameters
  • language (str): The manifest language to download, Default is english.
  • path (str | pathlib.Path): The path to save the manifest sqlite database. Example "D:/", Default is the current directory.
  • name (str): The manifest database file name. Default is manifest
  • force (bool): Whether to force the download. Default is False. However if set to true the old file will get removed and a new one will being to download.
Returns
  • None
Raises
  • FileNotFoundError: If the manifest file exists and force is False.
  • ValueError: If the provided language was not recognized.

2155    @abc.abstractmethod
2156    async def fetch_application_api_usage(
2157        self,
2158        access_token: str,
2159        application_id: int,
2160        /,
2161        *,
2162        start: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None,
2163        end: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None,
2164    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
2165        """Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.
2166
2167        Parameters
2168        ----------
2169        access_token : `str`
2170            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
2171        application_id : `int`
2172            The application id to get.
2173
2174        Other Parameters
2175        ----------------
2176        start : `typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]`
2177            A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage.
2178            This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.
2179
2180            If this is left to `None`. It will return the last 24 hours.
2181        end : `typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]`
2182            A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.
2183
2184            If this is left to `None`. It will return `now`.
2185
2186        Example
2187        -------
2188        ```py
2189        import datetime
2190
2191        # Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
2192        await fetch_application_api_usage(
2193            start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10), end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
2194        )
2195        ```
2196
2197        Returns
2198        -------
2199        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
2200            A JSON object of the application usage details.
2201        """

Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • application_id (int): The application id to get.
Other Parameters

  • start (typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]): A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage. This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.

    If this is left to None. It will return the last 24 hours.

  • end (typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]): A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.

    If this is left to None. It will return now.

Example
import datetime

# Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
await fetch_application_api_usage(
    start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10), end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
)

 580    # Records
 581
 582    @abc.abstractmethod
 583    def deserialize_records(
 584        self,
 585        payload: typedefs.JSONObject,
 586        scores: typing.Optional[records.RecordScores] = None,
 587        **nodes: int,
 588    ) -> records.Record:
 589        """Deserialize a JSON object of a profile record component.
 590
 591        Parameters
 592        ----------
 593        payload : `aiobungie.internal.helpers.JsonObject`
 594            The JSON object payload
 595        scores: `typing.Optional[records.RecordScores]`
 596            The records scores object.
 597            This exists only to keep the signature of `aiobungie.crates.CharacterRecord` with the record object.
 598            As it will always be `None` in that object.
 599        **nodes: `int`
 600            An int kwargs use to grab the node hashes while deserializing components.
 601
 602        Returns
 603        -------
 604        `aiobungie.records.Record`
 605            A standard implementation of a profile record component.
 606        """
